quotedConversation.text: Raped? Tough shit. The surveillance economy can‚Äôt prove consent but it will quickly enable people who want to criminalize women who don‚Äôt want to be forced to go through the life altering experience of forced pregnancy the ability to do so.

Ladies, the post roe America is going to require a radical rethinking of our engagement with the surveillance economy: no apps are safe. Remove every app from your phone. Delete any fertility apps immediately and encourage your friends to do the same.
You have no right to privacy. The surveillance economy is about to weaponized against half the population in states that over turn roe.

We need legislation NOW that bans surveillance advertising and behavioral based advertising and data collection. We need legislation NOW that bans ANY collection and sale of health related information currently not covered by existing legislation.
What happens if every service woman and female spouse registers with the exceptional family member program and requests reassignment out of states where reproductive medical care is restricted?
